docs.text: Welcome to ETL with ADF For full documentation visit Azure Data Factory Documentation . Azure Data Factory Facts & Tips Azure Data Factory (ADF) is Microsoft’s cloud-native service for managing batch data integration workloads ADF is a serverless cloud service – you create your ETL applications, but you don’t have to worry about infrastructure like operating systems or servers or how to manage changes in demand ADF has only a web based IDE called ADF UX . With an ADF UX , user can visually author and deploy resources for your data factory or Synapse pipelines without having to write any code Choosing the same location as your data factory reduces cost, because moving data out of one Azure region and into another incurs a bandwidth charge (sometimes referred to as an egress charge) ADF Tasks Link the Data Factory to the Git Repository Create Azure Storage Account
